      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Peak lists were filtered to retain those with an intensity threshold \u22650.05% of the maximum ion intensity of the total ion chromatogram... Datasets #4, #8, #10, #17, and #18 were binned with Cardinal MSI v2 at a bin width of 1 mDa... MSI data in imzML format or intensity matrices in CSV format can be imported to mass2adduct.",
      "asbval:note": "Cardinal is confirmed as used for MSI data preprocessing and binning. However, the specific conversion function cardinal2msimat() and the object types (MSProcessedImagingExperiment, MSContinuousImagingExperiment) are not mentioned in the passages. The paper states data can be imported 'via Cardinal' but does not detail the specific conversion mechanism claimed.",
