    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/cardinal-imaging-object-conversion/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MSI data in imzML format or intensity matrices in CSV format can be imported to mass2adduct. ... (1) mass2adduct takes all possible pairwise masses and calculates the mass difference for each pair. (2) A mass difference histogram is matched to a list of known mass differences to identify adducts. (3) Spatial correlation of m/z values is used to identify co-occurring metabolites. Then, a Pearson correlation coefficient is used to validate identified adducts.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms mass2adduct performs mass difference calculation and spatial correlation analysis, but does NOT name specific functions 'massdiff()', 'adductMatch()', or 'corrPairsMSI()'. The paper describes the workflow conceptually but does not document the R function API. The card invents function names.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
