    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Software to perform the adduct identification and correlation testing are implemented in an R package, mass2adduct. The software and installation instructions are available on GitHub at https://github.com/kbseah/mass2adduct... The intensity matrix was loaded into R, where correlations of adduct pairs were calculated.",
      "asbval:note": "R is confirmed as the execution environment for mass2adduct and correlation analysis. However, the specific dependencies (devtools, knitr, rmarkdown, pandoc) are not mentioned in the passages. The paper confirms R usage but does not detail these specific package dependencies.",
