    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MSI data in imzML format or intensity matrices in CSV format can be imported to mass2adduct... The input data needs to be generated with high mass accuracy (below 5 ppm) to allow for an accurate and reliable detection of \u0394mass for ion pairs.",
      "asbval:note": "Scope aligns with paper's description of input requirements and use case.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have preprocessed MSI data (as a CSV intensity matrix or Cardinal MSProcessedImagingExperiment object) and suspect that observed peaks include both parent ions and their adducts formed with matrix or salt species.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:22:52.850003+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The typically thousands of measured signals in metabolomics experiments often remain unidentified and have been described as dark metabolome... Adducts are expected to co-occur in the same spot as their parent metabolite for any given tissue sample. Consequently, calculating individual correlation values between the intensities of a peak and its putative adduct peak across all pixels of a MALDI-MSI dataset provides statistical support for MS1-based adduct identifications",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly addresses dark metabolome and spatial correlation validation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it to disambiguate the 'dark metabolome' of unexplained peaks in MALDI-MSI datasets and to validate putative adduct pairs using spatial correlation in imaging pixels.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:22:52.850003+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The input data needs to be generated with high mass accuracy (below 5 ppm) to allow for an accurate and reliable detection of \u0394mass for ion pairs. Detection of peaks in each single mass spectrum of an MSI dataset is a challenging task, and rigorous care should be taken to perform this step as accurate as possible.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper emphasizes preprocessing requirement and high mass accuracy.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input is unbinned, un-preprocessed raw instrument data (MS1 profiles)\u2014preprocess and peak-bin first using Cardinal or comparable software.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:22:52.850003+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For untargeted metabolomics approaches using liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry (LC-MS), da Silva et al. estimate that only 1.8% of the spectra can be annotated. Similarly, low numbers of spectra are expected to be annotated in MSI datasets.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper's focus on untargeted MSI and annotation of unidentified peaks supports this scope limitation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-peak-pair-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You are analyzing targeted metabolomics with a small, validated list of compounds\u2014adduct detection is most valuable for discovery-mode untargeted MSI.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:22:52.850003+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrum-histogram-interpretation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We applied this idea to high-mass-resolution MSI data collected in positive ionization mode by first calculating mass differences (\u0394mass) between all pairs of detected peaks in a MALDI-MSI dataset from a mouse brain tissue section (dataset #10) and then creating a histogram of all \u0394mass (see Figure 1A). We found high counts of \u0394mass of 21.985 and 37.955 Da, which matched the \u0394mass between [M + H]+ and [M + Na]+ or [M + K]+, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Core methodology confirmed: mass differences calculated, binned into histogram, peaks identified and matched to known adducts.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrum-histogram-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Bin calculated mass differences into a histogram with instrument-appropriate precision, then visually and statistically identify peaks representing abundant molecular adducts.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:23:13.563459+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrum-histogram-interpretation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We compiled a set of matrix-related adducts into a list of adducts and mass differences for typical chemical transformations to match calculated \u0394mass values of a dataset (see Supporting Table S1). We used the list to identify the number of possible adducts based on specific m/z differences for each ion pair in a dataset.",
      "asbval:note": "Histogram bins matched against known adduct mass differences to annotate adducts.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrum-histogram-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This technique transforms raw pairwise mass differences into actionable annotations by matching histogram bins to known chemical transformations.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:23:13.563459+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrum-histogram-interpretation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
