      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Peak lists and intensity matrices for datasets #1\u20133, #5\u20137, #9, #13\u201316, #19, and #20 were generated with SCiLS v2019b (Bruker, Germany), using 5 ppm bin width... Peak intensity matrices were exported in text CSV format... An intensity matrix for every ion of the respective peak list in each pixel on the dataset was exported with the software MSiReader v0.09.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SCiLS and MSiReader are used for data export and CSV export is performed, but does not explicitly state that CSV export is a requirement for mass2adduct import. The workflow description states 'MSI data in imzML format or intensity matrices in CSV format can be imported to mass2adduct' (passage 6), confirming CSV is one accepted format but not the only one.",
