    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrum-histogram-interpretation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Datasets #4, #8, #10, #17, and #18 were binned with Cardinal MSI v2 at a bin width of 1 mDa... MSI data in imzML format or intensity matrices in CSV format can be imported to mass2adduct. (1) mass2adduct takes all possible pairwise masses and calculates the mass difference for each pair.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Cardinal is used for MSI preprocessing and that mass2adduct accepts imzML format (which Cardinal can output). However, the paper does not mention 'MSProcessedImagingExperiment', 'MSContinuousImagingExperiment', or 'msimat format' conversion. The card's specific technical claims about object types and format conversion are not verified in the passages.",
