    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multiple-testing-correction-bonferroni/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Software to perform the adduct identification and correlation testing are implemented in an R package, mass2adduct. The software and installation instructions are available on GitHub at https://github.com/kbseah/mass2adduct",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms mass2adduct is an R package that performs correlation testing and is available on GitHub. However, the paper does not explicitly state that Bonferroni correction is 'built-in' to the package functions. The Bonferroni correction is described as part of the workflow/methodology (applied to p-values from correlation tests), but it is not clear whether this is automated within the package or performed separately by the user.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
