      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The mass difference was calculated for all pairs of peaks, and matched against a list of known adduct types... For each dataset, Pearson's two-sided correlation test was performed for all ion pairs using per-pixel intensity values.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the workflow (mass difference matching followed by correlation testing) but does not name the functions 'adductMatch' or 'diffGetPeaks'. The functional workflow is correct but function names are not verified.",
