    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-annotation-and-overlay-visualization/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For each dataset, Pearson's two-sided correlation test was performed for all ion pairs using per-pixel intensity values. We applied three different methods to screen for false positives: (1) The Bonferroni correction was applied to the p-values from the correlation test... (2) Uncorrected p-values for positively correlated pairs were used for false-discovery-rate analysis with the R package qvalue v2.10.1",
      "asbval:note": "Paper performs correlation testing and FDR analysis on ion pairs, but does not name the function corrPairsMSI() or describe massdiff/adductMatch object classes. The functional workflow exists but specific function/object names are not confirmed in passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-annotation-and-overlay-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After correlation testing has validated putative parent\u2013adduct ion pairs (e.g., via corrPairsMSI() on a massdiff object annotated with adductMatch results)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:25:08.620058+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-annotation-and-overlay-visualization/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The parent ion [PC(36:1) + H]+ showed a similarly strong ion intensity correlation to its matrix adduct [PC(36:1) + (DHB-H2O) + H]+ (corr. coeff. r = 0.779)... (Figure 1D). A positive correlation value alone does not guarantee that two ions are chemically related. However, in combination with our prior knowledge on sample and matrix composition, it provides additional confidence to screen for potential adducts.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms spatial co-localization is used to validate adduct pairs, but does not describe colored scatter plot visualization (red/blue points). Visualization is shown as correlation matrices and heatmaps, not overlaid scatter plots with contrasting symbols.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-0c04720",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-annotation-and-overlay-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "use this skill to annotate and visualize the mass spectrum plot to confirm that identified pairs exhibit expected overlap\u2014e.g., red points (adduct ions) spatially co-localized with blue points (parent ions) in the imaging data.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
