    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-annotation-and-overlay-visualization/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our workflow is available as a software package for R, called mass2adduct. It allows data import in various formats (e.g., imzML via Cardinal,29 intensity tables in CSV format), parallelization to speed up correlation testing, and several visualization tools.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms mass2adduct is an R package with visualization tools, but does not name the specific function pointsAdducts(). The paper states 'several visualization tools' exist but does not enumerate them or confirm pointsAdducts() by name.",
